  "notes": "HAR-262 captured Shopify Admin GraphQL 2026-04 BulkOperation reads, list empty filters, deprecated currentBulkOperation behavior, bulkOperationRunQuery validation, unknown-id cancel userErrors, terminal cancel userErrors, and safe query export status transitions. HAR-263 implements the local BulkOperation state/read/list/current/cancel foundation using that fixture evidence; HAR-346 promotes the read/cancel foundation to generic strict parity by seeding captured BulkOperation jobs into the local proxy harness, comparing empty read/list/current behavior, unknown and terminal cancel userErrors, local staged cancel, and read-after-local-cancel. HAR-264 promotes the product query export slice to executable parity by seeding captured Shopify JSONL product records, replaying bulkOperationRunQuery locally, comparing completed job shape/counters/result metadata to the captured terminal Shopify job, and verifying downstream read-after-run behavior. HAR-265 adds runtime-test-backed local bulkOperationRunMutation import staging for implemented Admin API inner mutations with local bulk-import executors, including staged upload handoff, result JSONL, unsupported-root failure, mutation-log ordering, and downstream read-after-write behavior. HAR-396 extends runtime evidence for malformed JSONL imports by proving FAILED mutation jobs keep result URLs and are visible through bulkOperation, bulkOperations, and currentBulkOperation without upstream passthrough. Exact Shopify import result-file schema and partial-failure status semantics still need live capture before broadening semantics beyond the locally supported executor boundary.",
